div.div:
Update null-checks and dependencies, expand autoload mapping
Null-check enhancements have been implemented for SyncAutumnFiles and AttachmentLists, improving command accuracy. The composer.json now reflects updated dependencies with the inclusion of mongodb. Additionally, AutoLoad mapping has been expanded to accommodate SyncAutumnFiles and AutumnFile models, and the Laravel reference in installed.php has been updated.

Correct case in namespaces references
The commit corrects the case of namespaces references in `SyncAutumnFiles.php`, `AutumnFile.php`, and `AttachmentLists.php`. The references were updated from 'app\Models' to 'App\Models' in all occasions, ensuring consistency and correct class mapping.

Add MongoDB-related operations and update PHP-CS configuration
This commit introduces new operations for handling MongoDB database queries and relations such as 'Aggregate', 'BelongsToMany', 'BelongsTo'. It also adds new exceptions associated with these operations. Additionally, a new PhpCsFixer configuration file is included which defines coding standards for the project.

Update Cors allowed_origin_fn parameters
This commit modifies the allowed_origin_fn function within the Cors wrapper. The function now takes two arguments instead of one to better match functional requirements.

Update Docker base image to Debian Bookworm
In this commit, the base image of the Dockerfile has been updated from Debian Bullseye to Debian Bookworm. This upgrade provides a more up-to-date and secure platform for running the application.
